sequenceDiagram
    participant CPU as CPU (Host)
    participant GPU as GPU (Device)
    participant MEM as GPU Memory (HBM)

    Note over CPU,MEM: WITHOUT fusion: many small kernels

    CPU->>GPU: Launch kernel: split_with_sizes
    GPU->>MEM: Read qkv from HBM
    GPU->>MEM: Write q, k, v to HBM

    CPU->>GPU: Launch kernel: rms_norm (q)
    GPU->>MEM: Read q from HBM
    GPU->>MEM: Write q_normed to HBM

    CPU->>GPU: Launch kernel: rms_norm (k)
    GPU->>MEM: Read k from HBM
    GPU->>MEM: Write k_normed to HBM

    CPU->>GPU: Launch kernel: rotary_embedding
    GPU->>MEM: Read q_normed, k_normed from HBM
    GPU->>MEM: Write q_rope, k_rope to HBM

    Note over CPU,MEM: WITH fusion: one big kernel

    CPU->>GPU: Launch kernel: fused_qk_norm_rope
    GPU->>MEM: Read qkv, weights, cos_sin from HBM
    GPU->>MEM: Write q_rope, k_rope, v to HBM
    Note over GPU,MEM: All intermediate data stays in<br/>registers/shared memory (fast!)
